#remove urls, clean, and lowercase text 
def clean_txt(txt_in):
    import re
    clean_str = re.sub("[^A-Za-z]+", " ", txt_in).strip().lower()
    clean_str =  re.sub(r"https\S+", "", str(txt_in))
    clean_str = clean_str.lower()
    return clean_str

def remove_punc(x):

#remove stopwords 
def my_stop_words(var_in):
    from nltk.corpus import stopwords
    more_words=['bcovid','covid','#coronavirus', '#coronavirusoutbreak', '#coronavirusPandemic', '#covid19', '#covid_19', '#epitwitter', '#ihavecorona', 'amp', 'coronavirus', 'covid19']
    stop_words=set(stopwords.words('english'))
    stop_words.update(more_words)
    tmp = [word for word in var_in.split() if word not in stop_words]
    tmp = ' '.join(tmp)
    return tmp
text3 = text3.apply(my_stop_words)
text3

#remove emoji
def remove_emoji(text):
    emoji_pattern = re.compile("["
                           u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"  
                           u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"  
                           u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"  
                           u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"  
                           u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
                           u"\U000024C2-\U0001F251"
                           "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
    return emoji_pattern.sub(r'', text)
text3 = text3.apply(remove_emoji)

# more clean 
def more_clean(text):
    text = re.sub('\[.*?\]', '', text)
    text = re.sub('https?://\S+|www\.\S+', '', text)
    text = re.sub('<.*?>+', '', text)
    text = re.sub('[%s]' % re.escape(string.punctuation), '', text)
    text = re.sub('\n', '', text)
    text = re.sub('\w*\d\w*', '', text)
    return text
text3 = text3.apply(more_clean)
text3
